The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) where \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X_i \leq 27.3) = 0.7\) for each observation \(X_i\), and since the distribution is continuous, \(P(X_i < 27.3) = 0.7\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven of the eight observations being less than 27.3. Let \(N\) be the number of observations less than or equal to 27.3, so \(N \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\). Then:
\[
P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(N \geq 7) = P(N=7) + P(N=8).
\]

Calculate each probability:
\[
P(N=7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]
\[
P(N=8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = 1 \times (0.7)^8 \times 1.
\]

First, compute \((0.7)^7\):
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543.
\]
Then:
\[
P(N=7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032.
