\[
(0.7)^8 = 0.7 \times (0.7)^7 = 0.7 \times 0.0823543 = 0.05764801.
\]
Then:
\[
P(N=8) = 0.05764801.
\]

Sum the probabilities:
\[
P(N \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.
\]

Rounding 0.25529833 to three significant figures gives 0.255. The inputs (percentile 27.3 and probability 0.7) suggest three significant figures are reasonable.

