**************
The probability of drawing a white chip, \(P(W)\), is calculated using the law of total probability. The formula is:  
\[ P(W) = P(W \mid B_1) \cdot P(B_1) + P(W \mid B_2) \cdot P(B_2) + P(W \mid B_3) \cdot P(B_3) + P(W \mid B_4) \cdot P(B_4) \]  

