- Of those with normal blood pressure (NBP), 11% have an irregular heartbeat. First, the percentage with normal blood pressure is 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%. Then, the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% of 65% = 0.11 × 65 = 7.15%.

